@Node BlurMotionAd "The Blur-Motion Machine"

    The Blur-Motion Machine is freely-distributable for all to enjoy.
But is not public domain.

    The Blur-Motion Machine uses several similar frames to create one
motion blurred image.  This effect can be very impressive, if you have
the rendering patience to create multiple frames for each desired
blurred image.

@EndNode

@Node FrameNamerAd "FrameNamer"

    Most of my scripts require animation images be in the name format
of pic.0001, pic.0002, pic.0003, etc..
    If your animation frames, perhaps created by a 3D program, are
not in the format of pic.0001, etc., there is a solution.  I have
created a script called FrameNamer.  FrameNamer easily converts
animation file name formats from any format to any format.  As long
as there is some sort of number system in your frame names, FrameName
can convert it quickly and easily.  Look for FNamer1.LHA on finer BBS
systems everywhere.

@EndNode

@Node AnimExtenderAd "AnimExtender"

    AnimExender lengthens your animations by duplicating the first
and/or last frames of your animations.  It's also a quick and easy
way of creating an animation out of a single frame, should you wish
to create, say, particles on a static backdrop.  Simple, eh?
    Look for AnimExtd11c.LHA (AnimExtd.LHA on Aminet) in finer BBSs
everywhere.  Make sure you're using at least v1.1c.  Earlier versions
were buggy.

@EndNode
